# Gateway path-routing registry — ROUTABLE NEURON TARGETS (ADR 0017 §Next).
# ==========================================================================
# The gateway publishes ONE path-routing surface on :8443:
#
#     https://<host>:8443/{bundle}/{neuron}/<whatever the neuron serves>
#
# The gateway owns ONLY the /{bundle}/{neuron}/ prefix: it matches that, resolves the
# neuron's service on neuron_net at REQUEST time via Docker DNS, and forwards the rest of
# the path/method/body UNTOUCHED. `{neuron}` is the neuron's CONFIG name = its compose
# service name = its neuron_net DNS name (e.g. action_neuron_api).
#
# ADMISSION is governed by brain.env ACTION_ROUTE_ALLOW:
#   any       (DEFAULT) permit-any — every /{bundle}/{neuron}/ target routes. This file is
#             then only needed to OVERRIDE a target's internal serve port (default 8080).
#   registry  default-deny — ONLY the {bundle}/{neuron} targets listed below route; anything
#             else -> uniform JSON 404. (Firewall posture: the deployer opts into restriction.)
#
# FORMAT (one target per line; blank / #-comment lines ignored):
#   {bundle}/{neuron} = <internal-serve-port>
# The port defaults to 8080 (action.py --serve default) when a target is unlisted, so under
# permit-any a standard action neuron needs NO entry here at all. List a target to (a) pin a
# non-8080 serve port, and/or (b) admit it when ACTION_ROUTE_ALLOW=registry.
#
# NOTE — external ports are elsewhere. This file is INTERNAL serve ports (path-multiplexed
# behind one :8443 listener — they never conflict). The gateway's PUBLISHED host ports (the
# 1:1 external->container map: :8000 / :11434 / :8443) live in brain.env posture
# (CHROMA_GATEWAY_PORT / OLLAMA_GW_PORT / ACTION_GW_PORT); gateway_config.py fails closed if
# two exposed listeners claim the same host port.
#
# Example (uncomment to pin a non-default port or to seed a restrict-list):
#   example_neuron_bundle/action_neuron_api = 8080
